For the purpose of subsection (1) of this section, “revenue” means any income or return accruing to or derived by the Government of the Federation from any source and includes-any receipt, however described, arising from the operation of any law;any return, however described, arising from or in respect of any property held by the Government of the Federation;any return by way of interest on loans and dividends in respect of shares or interest held by the Government of the Federation in any company or statutory body.
