A public officer shall not put himself in a position where his personal interest conflicts with his duties and responsibilities.
Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing paragraph, a public officer shall not-receive or be paid the emoluments of any public office at the same time as he receives or is paid the emoluments of any other public office; orexcept where he is not employed on full time basis, engage or participate in the management or running of any private business, profession or trade but nothing in this sub-paragraph shall prevent a public officer from engaging in farming.
